  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add the<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>in half lengthways, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add the <strong>chopped leek</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Cook for 5 min further or until the leek has softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 20-25 min or until most of the stock is absorbed and the rice is almost cooked</p><p>Grate the <strong>brie </strong>coarsely (or roughly chop into small cubes)</p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>dried cranberries</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, bash the <strong>pecans</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>into small pieces (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p><p>Add the <strong>crushed pecans</strong> to a baking tray lined with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> and drizzle over <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>honey </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3 min or until golden and crunchy – these are your <strong>honey roasted pecans</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk so they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is almost cooked, add the <strong>grated brie</strong>,<strong> </strong>half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all] </span>the <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>to the pan</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the rest of the wholegrain mustard for another recipe!</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min further or until the rice is cooked with a slight bite – this is your <strong>brie & leek risotto</strong></p><p>Wash the<strong> rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/brie-and-leek-risotto-with-honey-roasted-pecans/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>brie & leek risotto </strong>topped with the<strong> honey roasted pecans </strong>and <strong>chopped cranberries</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>rocket </strong>and drizzle over the<strong> remaining honey</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
